---

<section
  id="philosophy"
  class="relative bg-brand-bg"
  aria-labelledby="philosophy-heading"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-28 sm:px-10 sm:py-36 lg:px-16 lg:py-48">
    <div
      class="grid gap-y-12 lg:grid-cols-12 lg:gap-x-12 xl:gap-x-20"
    >
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <p class="caption text-brand-accent">Our Philosophy</p>
        <div class="mt-6 hairline max-w-[3rem]"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-8">
        <h2
          id="philosophy-heading"
          class="max-w-3xl text-balance font-serif text-4xl leading-[1.05] sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
        >
          An older idea, <em
            class="not-italic font-serif italic text-brand-accent"
          >
            taken seriously.
          </em>
        </h2>

        <div
          class="mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-primary/80 sm:text-xl"
        >
          <p>
            The modern dog is too often under-asked and over-managed. We
            work from a simpler proposition: that the right relationship
            is built on shared experience &mdash; long mornings on the trail,
            deliberate stillness in the home, and an unhurried trust earned
            over time.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not produce obedient pets. We help families recover
            something quieter, more useful, and a lot more fun.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="caption mt-12 text-brand-primary/55">
          &mdash; Campbell K9s, Est. New England
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
